98 DILocation *DILocation::getMergedLocations(ArrayRef Locs) { 0
99 if (Locs.empty()) 0
100 return nullptr; 0
101 if (Locs.size() == 1) 0
102 return Locs[0]; 0
103 auto *Merged = Locs[0]; 0
104 for (DILocation *L : llvm::drop_begin(Locs)) { 0
105 Merged = getMergedLocation(Merged, L); 0
106 if (Merged == nullptr) 0
107 break; 0
108 } ----

112 DILocation *DILocation::getMergedLocation(DILocation *LocA, DILocation *LocB) { 0
113 if (!LocA || !LocB) 0
114 return nullptr; 0
115 ----
116 if (LocA == LocB) 0
117 return LocA; 0
118 ----
119 LLVMContext &C = LocA->getContext(); 0
120 ----
121 using LocVec = SmallVector; ----
122 LocVec ALocs; 0
123 LocVec BLocs; 0
124 SmallDenseMap, unsigned, ----
125 4> ----
126 ALookup; 0
127 ----
128 // Walk through LocA and its inlined-at locations, populate them in ALocs and ----
129 // save the index for the subprogram and inlined-at pair, which we use to find ----
130 // a matching starting location in LocB's chain. ----
131 for (auto [L, I] = std::make_pair(LocA, 0U); L; L = L->getInlinedAt(), I++) { 0
132 ALocs.push_back(L); 0
133 auto Res = ALookup.try_emplace( 0
134 {L->getScope()->getSubprogram(), L->getInlinedAt()}, I); 0
135 assert(Res.second && "Multiple pairs in a location chain?"); 0
136 (void)Res; ----
137 } ----
138 ----
139 LocVec::reverse_iterator ARIt = ALocs.rend(); 0
140 LocVec::reverse_iterator BRIt = BLocs.rend(); 0
141 ----
142 // Populate BLocs and look for a matching starting location, the first ----
143 // location with the same subprogram and inlined-at location as in LocA's ----
144 // chain. Since the two locations have the same inlined-at location we do ----
145 // not need to look at those parts of the chains. ----
146 for (auto [L, I] = std::make_pair(LocB, 0U); L; L = L->getInlinedAt(), I++) { 0
147 BLocs.push_back(L); 0
148 ----
149 if (ARIt != ALocs.rend()) 0
150 // We have already found a matching starting location. ----
151 continue; 0
152 ----
153 auto IT = ALookup.find({L->getScope()->getSubprogram(), L->getInlinedAt()}); 0
154 if (IT == ALookup.end()) 0
155 continue; 0
156 ----
157 // The + 1 is to account for the &*rev_it = &(it - 1) relationship. ----
158 ARIt = LocVec::reverse_iterator(ALocs.begin() + IT->second + 1); 0
159 BRIt = LocVec::reverse_iterator(BLocs.begin() + I + 1); 0
160 ----
161 // If we have found a matching starting location we do not need to add more ----
162 // locations to BLocs, since we will only look at location pairs preceding ----
163 // the matching starting location, and adding more elements to BLocs could ----
164 // invalidate the iterator that we initialized here. ----
165 break; 0
166 } ----
167 ----
168 // Merge the two locations if possible, using the supplied ----
169 // inlined-at location for the created location. ----
170 auto MergeLocPair = [&C](const DILocation *L1, const DILocation *L2, 0
171 DILocation *InlinedAt) -> DILocation * { 0
172 if (L1 == L2) 0
173 return DILocation::get(C, L1->getLine(), L1->getColumn(), L1->getScope(), 0
174 InlinedAt); 0
175 ----
176 // If the locations originate from different subprograms we can't produce ----
177 // a common location. ----
178 if (L1->getScope()->getSubprogram() != L2->getScope()->getSubprogram()) 0
179 return nullptr; 0
180 ----
181 // Return the nearest common scope inside a subprogram. ----
182 auto GetNearestCommonScope = [](DIScope *S1, DIScope *S2) -> DIScope * { 0
183 SmallPtrSet Scopes; 0
184 for (; S1; S1 = S1->getScope()) { 0
185 Scopes.insert(S1); 0
186 if (isa(S1)) 0
187 break; 0
188 } ----
189 ----
190 for (; S2; S2 = S2->getScope()) { 0
191 if (Scopes.count(S2)) 0
192 return S2; 0
193 if (isa(S2)) 0
194 break; 0
195 } ----
196 ----
197 return nullptr; 0
198 }; 0
199 ----
200 auto Scope = GetNearestCommonScope(L1->getScope(), L2->getScope()); 0
201 assert(Scope && "No common scope in the same subprogram?"); 0
202 ----
203 bool SameLine = L1->getLine() == L2->getLine(); 0
204 bool SameCol = L1->getColumn() == L2->getColumn(); 0
205 unsigned Line = SameLine ? L1->getLine() : 0; 0
206 unsigned Col = SameLine && SameCol ? L1->getColumn() : 0; 0
207 ----
208 return DILocation::get(C, Line, Col, Scope, InlinedAt); 0
209 }; 0
210 ----
211 DILocation *Result = ARIt != ALocs.rend() ? (*ARIt)->getInlinedAt() : nullptr; 0
212 ----
213 // If we have found a common starting location, walk up the inlined-at chains ----
214 // and try to produce common locations. ----
215 for (; ARIt != ALocs.rend() && BRIt != BLocs.rend(); ++ARIt, ++BRIt) { 0
216 DILocation *Tmp = MergeLocPair(*ARIt, *BRIt, Result); 0
217 ----
218 if (!Tmp) 0
219 // We have walked up to a point in the chains where the two locations ----
220 // are irreconsilable. At this point Result contains the nearest common ----
221 // location in the inlined-at chains of LocA and LocB, so we break here. ----
222 break; 0
223 ----
224 Result = Tmp; 0
225 } ----
226 ----
227 if (Result) 0
228 return Result; 0
229 ----
230 // We ended up with LocA and LocB as irreconsilable locations. Produce a ----
231 // location at 0:0 with one of the locations' scope. The function has ----
232 // historically picked A's scope, and a nullptr inlined-at location, so that ----
233 // behavior is mimicked here but I am not sure if this is always the correct ----
234 // way to handle this. ----
235 return DILocation::get(C, 0, 0, LocA->getScope(), nullptr); 0
236 } 0

238 std::optional ----
239 DILocation::encodeDiscriminator(unsigned BD, unsigned DF, unsigned CI) { 0
240 std::array Components = {BD, DF, CI}; 0
241 uint64_t RemainingWork = 0U; 0
242 // We use RemainingWork to figure out if we have no remaining components to ----
243 // encode. For example: if BD != 0 but DF == 0 && CI == 0, we don't need to ----
244 // encode anything for the latter 2. ----
245 // Since any of the input components is at most 32 bits, their sum will be ----
246 // less than 34 bits, and thus RemainingWork won't overflow. ----
247 RemainingWork = ----
248 std::accumulate(Components.begin(), Components.end(), RemainingWork); 0
249 ----
250 int I = 0; 0
251 unsigned Ret = 0; 0
252 unsigned NextBitInsertionIndex = 0; 0
253 while (RemainingWork > 0) { 0
254 unsigned C = Components[I++]; 0
255 RemainingWork -= C; 0
256 unsigned EC = encodeComponent(C); 0
257 Ret |= (EC << NextBitInsertionIndex); 0
258 NextBitInsertionIndex += encodingBits(C); 0
259 } ----
260 ----
261 // Encoding may be unsuccessful because of overflow. We determine success by ----
262 // checking equivalence of components before & after encoding. Alternatively, ----
263 // we could determine Success during encoding, but the current alternative is ----
264 // simpler. ----
265 unsigned TBD, TDF, TCI = 0; 0
266 decodeDiscriminator(Ret, TBD, TDF, TCI); 0
267 if (TBD == BD && TDF == DF && TCI == CI) 0
268 return Ret; 0
269 return std::nullopt; 0
270 } ----

272 void DILocation::decodeDiscriminator(unsigned D, unsigned &BD, unsigned &DF, 0
273 unsigned &CI) { ----
274 BD = getUnsignedFromPrefixEncoding(D); 0
275 DF = getUnsignedFromPrefixEncoding(getNextComponentInDiscriminator(D)); 0
276 CI = getUnsignedFromPrefixEncoding( 0
277 getNextComponentInDiscriminator(getNextComponentInDiscriminator(D))); ----
278 } 0

298 DINode::DIFlags DINode::splitFlags(DIFlags Flags, 0
299 SmallVectorImpl &SplitFlags) { ----
300 // Flags that are packed together need to be specially handled, so ----
301 // that, for example, we emit "DIFlagPublic" and not ----
302 // "DIFlagPrivate | DIFlagProtected". ----
303 if (DIFlags A = Flags & FlagAccessibility) { 0
304 if (A == FlagPrivate) 0
305 SplitFlags.push_back(FlagPrivate); 0
306 else if (A == FlagProtected) 0
307 SplitFlags.push_back(FlagProtected); 0
308 else ----
309 SplitFlags.push_back(FlagPublic); 0
310 Flags &= ~A; 0
311 } ----
312 if (DIFlags R = Flags & FlagPtrToMemberRep) { 0
313 if (R == FlagSingleInheritance) 0
314 SplitFlags.push_back(FlagSingleInheritance); 0
315 else if (R == FlagMultipleInheritance) 0
316 SplitFlags.push_back(FlagMultipleInheritance); 0
317 else ----
318 SplitFlags.push_back(FlagVirtualInheritance); 0
319 Flags &= ~R; 0
320 } ----
321 if ((Flags & FlagIndirectVirtualBase) == FlagIndirectVirtualBase) { 0
322 Flags &= ~FlagIndirectVirtualBase; 0
323 SplitFlags.push_back(FlagIndirectVirtualBase); 0
324 } ----
325 ----
326 #define HANDLE_DI_FLAG(ID, NAME) \ ----
327 if (DIFlags Bit = Flags & Flag##NAME) { \ ----
328 SplitFlags.push_back(Bit); \ ----
329 Flags &= ~Bit; \ ----
330 } ----
331 #include "llvm/IR/DebugInfoFlags.def" ----
332 return Flags; 0
333 } ----

775 DICompositeType *DICompositeType::buildODRType( 0
776 LLVMContext &Context, MDString &Identifier, unsigned Tag, MDString *Name, ----
777 Metadata *File, unsigned Line, Metadata *Scope, Metadata *BaseType, ----
778 uint64_t SizeInBits, uint32_t AlignInBits, uint64_t OffsetInBits, ----
779 DIFlags Flags, Metadata *Elements, unsigned RuntimeLang, ----
780 Metadata *VTableHolder, Metadata *TemplateParams, Metadata *Discriminator, ----
781 Metadata *DataLocation, Metadata *Associated, Metadata *Allocated, ----
782 Metadata *Rank, Metadata *Annotations) { ----
783 assert(!Identifier.getString().empty() && "Expected valid identifier"); 0
784 if (!Context.isODRUniquingDebugTypes()) 0
785 return nullptr; 0
786 auto *&CT = (*Context.pImpl->DITypeMap)[&Identifier]; 0
787 if (!CT) 0
788 return CT = DICompositeType::getDistinct( 0
789 Context, Tag, Name, File, Line, Scope, BaseType, SizeInBits, ----
790 AlignInBits, OffsetInBits, Flags, Elements, RuntimeLang, ----
791 VTableHolder, TemplateParams, &Identifier, Discriminator, ----
792 DataLocation, Associated, Allocated, Rank, Annotations); 0
793 ----
794 if (CT->getTag() != Tag) 0
795 return nullptr; 0
796 ----
797 // Only mutate CT if it's a forward declaration and the new operands aren't. ----
798 assert(CT->getRawIdentifier() == &Identifier && "Wrong ODR identifier?"); 0
799 if (!CT->isForwardDecl() || (Flags & DINode::FlagFwdDecl)) 0
800 return CT; 0
801 ----
802 // Mutate CT in place. Keep this in sync with getImpl. ----
803 CT->mutate(Tag, Line, RuntimeLang, SizeInBits, AlignInBits, OffsetInBits, 0
804 Flags); ----
805 Metadata *Ops[] = {File, Scope, Name, BaseType, ----
806 Elements, VTableHolder, TemplateParams, &Identifier, ----
807 Discriminator, DataLocation, Associated, Allocated, ----
808 Rank, Annotations}; 0
809 assert((std::end(Ops) - std::begin(Ops)) == (int)CT->getNumOperands() && 0
810 "Mismatched number of operands"); ----
811 for (unsigned I = 0, E = CT->getNumOperands(); I != E; ++I) 0
812 if (Ops[I] != CT->getOperand(I)) 0
813 CT->setOperand(I, Ops[I]); 0
814 return CT; 0
815 } ----

1014 DISubprogram::DISPFlags ----
1015 DISubprogram::toSPFlags(bool IsLocalToUnit, bool IsDefinition, bool IsOptimized, 0
1016 unsigned Virtuality, bool IsMainSubprogram) { ----
1017 // We're assuming virtuality is the low-order field. ----
1018 static_assert(int(SPFlagVirtual) == int(dwarf::DW_VIRTUALITY_virtual) && ----
1019 int(SPFlagPureVirtual) == ----
1020 int(dwarf::DW_VIRTUALITY_pure_virtual), ----
1021 "Virtuality constant mismatch"); ----
1022 return static_cast( ----
1023 (Virtuality & SPFlagVirtuality) | 0
1024 (IsLocalToUnit ? SPFlagLocalToUnit : SPFlagZero) | 0
1025 (IsDefinition ? SPFlagDefinition : SPFlagZero) | 0
1026 (IsOptimized ? SPFlagOptimized : SPFlagZero) | 0
1027 (IsMainSubprogram ? SPFlagMainSubprogram : SPFlagZero)); 0
1028 } ----

1041 ----
1042 DILocalScope *DILocalScope::cloneScopeForSubprogram( 0
1043 DILocalScope &RootScope, DISubprogram &NewSP, LLVMContext &Ctx, ----
1044 DenseMap &Cache) { ----
1045 SmallVector ScopeChain; 0
1046 DIScope *CachedResult = nullptr; 0
1047 ----
1048 for (DIScope *Scope = &RootScope; !isa(Scope); 0
1049 Scope = Scope->getScope()) { 0
1050 if (auto It = Cache.find(Scope); It != Cache.end()) { 0
1051 CachedResult = cast(It->second); 0
1052 break; 0
1053 } ----
1054 ScopeChain.push_back(Scope); 0
1055 } ----
1056 ----
1057 // Recreate the scope chain, bottom-up, starting at the new subprogram (or a ----
1058 // cached result). ----
1059 DIScope *UpdatedScope = CachedResult ? CachedResult : &NewSP; 0
1060 for (DIScope *ScopeToUpdate : reverse(ScopeChain)) { 0
1061 TempMDNode ClonedScope = ScopeToUpdate->clone(); 0
1062 cast(*ClonedScope).replaceScope(UpdatedScope); 0
1063 UpdatedScope = ----
1064 cast(MDNode::replaceWithUniqued(std::move(ClonedScope))); 0
1065 Cache[ScopeToUpdate] = UpdatedScope; 0
1066 } 0
1067 ----
1068 return cast(UpdatedScope); 0
1069 } 0

1073 #define HANDLE_DISP_FLAG(ID, NAME) .Case("DISPFlag" #NAME, SPFlag##NAME) ----
1074 #include "llvm/IR/DebugInfoFlags.def" ----
1075 .Default(SPFlagZero); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1076 } ----

1086 #include "llvm/IR/DebugInfoFlags.def" ----
1087 } ----
1088 return ""; 0

1090 ----
1091 DISubprogram::DISPFlags ----
1092 DISubprogram::splitFlags(DISPFlags Flags, 0
1093 SmallVectorImpl &SplitFlags) { ----
1094 // Multi-bit fields can require special handling. In our case, however, the ----
1095 // only multi-bit field is virtuality, and all its values happen to be ----
1096 // single-bit values, so the right behavior just falls out. ----
1097 #define HANDLE_DISP_FLAG(ID, NAME) \ ----
1098 if (DISPFlags Bit = Flags & SPFlag##NAME) { \ ----
1099 SplitFlags.push_back(Bit); \ ----
1100 Flags &= ~Bit; \ ----
1101 } ----
1102 #include "llvm/IR/DebugInfoFlags.def" ----
1103 return Flags; 0
1104 } ----

1304 AlignInBits(AlignInBits) {} 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1305 std::optional DIVariable::getSizeInBits() const { 0
1306 // This is used by the Verifier so be mindful of broken types. ----
1307 const Metadata *RawType = getRawType(); 0
1308 while (RawType) { 0
1309 // Try to get the size directly. ----
1310 if (auto *T = dyn_cast(RawType)) 0
1311 if (uint64_t Size = T->getSizeInBits()) 0
1312 return Size; 0
1313 ----
1314 if (auto *DT = dyn_cast(RawType)) { 0
1315 // Look at the base type. ----
1316 RawType = DT->getRawBaseType(); 0
1317 continue; 0
1318 } ----
1319 ----
1320 // Missing type or size. ----
1321 break; 0
1322 } ----
1323 ----
1324 // Fail gracefully. ----
1325 return std::nullopt; 0
1326 } ----

1389 bool DIExpression::isValid() const { 31 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1390 for (auto I = expr_op_begin(), E = expr_op_end(); I != E; ++I) { 31 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1391 // Check that there's space for the operand. ----
1392 if (I->get() + I->getSize() > E->get()) 0
1393 return false; 0
1394 ----
1395 uint64_t Op = I->getOp(); 0
1396 if ((Op >= dwarf::DW_OP_reg0 && Op <= dwarf::DW_OP_reg31) || 0
1397 (Op >= dwarf::DW_OP_breg0 && Op <= dwarf::DW_OP_breg31)) 0
1398 return true; 0
1399 ----
1400 // Check that the operand is valid. ----
1401 switch (Op) { 0
1402 default: 0
1403 return false; 0
1404 case dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_fragment: 0
1405 // A fragment operator must appear at the end. ----
1406 return I->get() + I->getSize() == E->get(); 0
1407 case dwarf::DW_OP_stack_value: { 0
1408 // Must be the last one or followed by a DW_OP_LLVM_fragment. ----
1409 if (I->get() + I->getSize() == E->get()) 0
1410 break; 0
1411 auto J = I; 0
1412 if ((++J)->getOp() != dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_fragment) 0
1413 return false; 0
1414 break; 0
1415 } ----
1416 case dwarf::DW_OP_swap: { 0
1417 // Must be more than one implicit element on the stack. ----
1418 ----
1419 // FIXME: A better way to implement this would be to add a local variable ----
1420 // that keeps track of the stack depth and introduce something like a ----
1421 // DW_LLVM_OP_implicit_location as a placeholder for the location this ----
1422 // DIExpression is attached to, or else pass the number of implicit stack ----
1423 // elements into isValid. ----
1424 if (getNumElements() == 1) 0
1425 return false; 0
1426 break; 0
1427 } ----
1428 case dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_entry_value: { 0
1429 // An entry value operator must appear at the beginning or immediately ----
1430 // following `DW_OP_LLVM_arg 0`, and the number of operations it cover can ----
1431 // currently only be 1, because we support only entry values of a simple ----
1432 // register location. One reason for this is that we currently can't ----
1433 // calculate the size of the resulting DWARF block for other expressions. ----
1434 auto FirstOp = expr_op_begin(); 0
1435 if (FirstOp->getOp() == dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_arg && FirstOp->getArg(0) == 0) 0
1436 ++FirstOp; 0
1437 return I->get() == FirstOp->get() && I->getArg(0) == 1; 0
1438 } ----
1439 case dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_implicit_pointer: 0
1440 case dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_convert: ----
1441 case dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_arg: ----
1442 case dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_tag_offset: ----
1443 case dwarf::DW_OP_constu: ----
1444 case dwarf::DW_OP_plus_uconst: ----
1445 case dwarf::DW_OP_plus: ----
1446 case dwarf::DW_OP_minus: ----
1447 case dwarf::DW_OP_mul: ----
1448 case dwarf::DW_OP_div: ----
1449 case dwarf::DW_OP_mod: ----
1450 case dwarf::DW_OP_or: ----
1451 case dwarf::DW_OP_and: ----
1452 case dwarf::DW_OP_xor: ----
1453 case dwarf::DW_OP_shl: ----
1454 case dwarf::DW_OP_shr: ----
1455 case dwarf::DW_OP_shra: ----
1456 case dwarf::DW_OP_deref: ----
1457 case dwarf::DW_OP_deref_size: ----
1458 case dwarf::DW_OP_xderef: ----
1459 case dwarf::DW_OP_lit0: ----
1460 case dwarf::DW_OP_not: ----
1461 case dwarf::DW_OP_dup: ----
1462 case dwarf::DW_OP_regx: ----
1463 case dwarf::DW_OP_bregx: ----
1464 case dwarf::DW_OP_push_object_address: ----
1465 case dwarf::DW_OP_over: ----
1466 case dwarf::DW_OP_consts: ----
1467 case dwarf::DW_OP_eq: ----
1468 case dwarf::DW_OP_ne: ----
1469 case dwarf::DW_OP_gt: ----
1470 case dwarf::DW_OP_ge: ----
1471 case dwarf::DW_OP_lt: ----
1472 case dwarf::DW_OP_le: ----
1473 break; 0
1474 } ----
1475 } ----
1476 return true; 31 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll

1479 bool DIExpression::isImplicit() const { 0
1480 if (!isValid()) 0
1481 return false; 0
1482 ----
1483 if (getNumElements() == 0) 0
1484 return false; 0
1485 ----
1486 for (const auto &It : expr_ops()) { 0
1487 switch (It.getOp()) { 0
1488 default: 0
1489 break; 0
1490 case dwarf::DW_OP_stack_value: 0
1491 case dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_tag_offset: ----
1492 return true; 0
1493 } ----
1494 } ----
1495 ----
1496 return false; 0

1498 ----
1499 bool DIExpression::isComplex() const { 0
1500 if (!isValid()) 0
1501 return false; 0
1502 ----
1503 if (getNumElements() == 0) 0
1504 return false; 0
1505 ----
1506 // If there are any elements other than fragment or tag_offset, then some ----
1507 // kind of complex computation occurs. ----
1508 for (const auto &It : expr_ops()) { 0
1509 switch (It.getOp()) { 0
1510 case dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_tag_offset: 0
1511 case dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_fragment: ----
1512 case dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_arg: ----
1513 continue; 0
1514 default: 0
1515 return true; 0
1516 } ----
1517 } ----
1518 ----
1519 return false; 0
1520 } ----
1521 ----
1522 bool DIExpression::isSingleLocationExpression() const { 0
1523 if (!isValid()) 0
1524 return false; 0
1525 ----
1526 if (getNumElements() == 0) 0
1527 return true; 0
1528 ----
1529 auto ExprOpBegin = expr_ops().begin(); 0
1530 auto ExprOpEnd = expr_ops().end(); 0
1531 if (ExprOpBegin->getOp() == dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_arg) 0
1532 ++ExprOpBegin; 0
1533 ----
1534 return !std::any_of(ExprOpBegin, ExprOpEnd, [](auto Op) { 0
1535 return Op.getOp() == dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_arg; 0
1536 }); 0
1537 } ----

1549 const DIExpression * ----
1550 DIExpression::convertToVariadicExpression(const DIExpression *Expr) { 0
1551 if (any_of(Expr->expr_ops(), [](auto ExprOp) { 0
1552 return ExprOp.getOp() == dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_arg; 0
1553 })) ----
1554 return Expr; 0
1555 SmallVector NewOps; 0
1556 NewOps.reserve(Expr->getNumElements() + 2); 0
1557 NewOps.append({dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_arg, 0}); 0
1558 NewOps.append(Expr->elements_begin(), Expr->elements_end()); 0
1559 return DIExpression::get(Expr->getContext(), NewOps); 0
1560 } 0
1561 ----
1562 std::optional ----
1563 DIExpression::convertToNonVariadicExpression(const DIExpression *Expr) { 0
1564 // Check for `isValid` covered by `isSingleLocationExpression`. ----
1565 if (!Expr->isSingleLocationExpression()) 0
1566 return std::nullopt; 0
1567 ----
1568 // An empty expression is already non-variadic. ----
1569 if (!Expr->getNumElements()) 0
1570 return Expr; 0
1571 ----
1572 auto ElementsBegin = Expr->elements_begin(); 0
1573 // If Expr does not have a leading DW_OP_LLVM_arg then we don't need to do ----
1574 // anything. ----
1575 if (*ElementsBegin != dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_arg) 0
1576 return Expr; 0
1577 ----
1578 SmallVector NonVariadicOps( ----
1579 make_range(ElementsBegin + 2, Expr->elements_end())); 0
1580 return DIExpression::get(Expr->getContext(), NonVariadicOps); 0
1581 } 0
1582 ----
1583 void DIExpression::canonicalizeExpressionOps(SmallVectorImpl &Ops, 0
1584 const DIExpression *Expr, ----
1585 bool IsIndirect) { ----
1586 // If Expr is not already variadic, insert the implied `DW_OP_LLVM_arg 0` ----
1587 // to the existing expression ops. ----
1588 if (none_of(Expr->expr_ops(), [](auto ExprOp) { 0
1589 return ExprOp.getOp() == dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_arg; 0

1722 DIExpression *DIExpression::appendOpsToArg(const DIExpression *Expr, 0
1723 ArrayRef Ops, ----
1724 unsigned ArgNo, bool StackValue) { ----

1732 SmallVector NewOps(Ops.begin(), Ops.end()); 0

1735 ----
1736 SmallVector NewOps; 0
1737 for (auto Op : Expr->expr_ops()) { 0
1738 // A DW_OP_stack_value comes at the end, but before a DW_OP_LLVM_fragment. ----
1739 if (StackValue) { 0

1757 DIExpression *DIExpression::replaceArg(const DIExpression *Expr, 0
1758 uint64_t OldArg, uint64_t NewArg) { ----
1759 assert(Expr && "Can't replace args in this expression"); 0
1760 ----
1761 SmallVector NewOps; 0
1762 ----

1765 Op.appendToVector(NewOps); 0
1766 continue; 0
1767 } ----
1768 NewOps.push_back(dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_arg); 0

1770 // OldArg has been deleted from the Op list, so decrement all indices ----
1771 // greater than it. ----

1779 DIExpression *DIExpression::prependOpcodes(const DIExpression *Expr, 0

1812 DIExpression *DIExpression::append(const DIExpression *Expr, 0
1813 ArrayRef Ops) { ----

1820 if (Op.getOp() == dwarf::DW_OP_stack_value || 0
1821 Op.getOp() == dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_fragment) { 0
1822 NewOps.append(Ops.begin(), Ops.end()); 0
1823 ----

1825 Ops = std::nullopt; 0
1826 } ----

1828 } ----

1832 assert(result->isValid() && "concatenated expression is not valid"); 0
1833 return result; 0

1835 ----
1836 DIExpression *DIExpression::appendToStack(const DIExpression *Expr, 0
1837 ArrayRef Ops) { ----
1838 assert(Expr && !Ops.empty() && "Can't append ops to this expression"); 0
1839 assert(none_of(Ops, 0
1840 [](uint64_t Op) { ----
1841 return Op == dwarf::DW_OP_stack_value || ----
1842 Op == dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_fragment; ----
1843 }) && ----
1844 "Can't append this op"); ----
1845 ----
1846 // Append a DW_OP_deref after Expr's current op list if it's non-empty and ----
1847 // has no DW_OP_stack_value. ----
1848 // ----
1849 // Match .* DW_OP_stack_value (DW_OP_LLVM_fragment A B)?. ----
1850 std::optional FI = Expr->getFragmentInfo(); 0
1851 unsigned DropUntilStackValue = FI ? 3 : 0; 0
1852 ArrayRef ExprOpsBeforeFragment = ----
1853 Expr->getElements().drop_back(DropUntilStackValue); 0
1854 bool NeedsDeref = (Expr->getNumElements() > DropUntilStackValue) && 0
1855 (ExprOpsBeforeFragment.back() != dwarf::DW_OP_stack_value); 0
1856 bool NeedsStackValue = NeedsDeref || ExprOpsBeforeFragment.empty(); 0
1857 ----
1858 // Append a DW_OP_deref after Expr's current op list if needed, then append ----
1859 // the new ops, and finally ensure that a single DW_OP_stack_value is present. ----
1860 SmallVector NewOps; 0
1861 if (NeedsDeref) 0
1862 NewOps.push_back(dwarf::DW_OP_deref); 0
1863 NewOps.append(Ops.begin(), Ops.end()); 0
1864 if (NeedsStackValue) 0
1865 NewOps.push_back(dwarf::DW_OP_stack_value); 0
1866 return DIExpression::append(Expr, NewOps); 0
1867 } 0

1869 std::optional DIExpression::createFragmentExpression( 0
1870 const DIExpression *Expr, unsigned OffsetInBits, unsigned SizeInBits) { ----
1871 SmallVector Ops; 0
1872 // Track whether it's safe to split the value at the top of the DWARF stack, ----
1873 // assuming that it'll be used as an implicit location value. ----
1874 bool CanSplitValue = true; 0
1875 // Copy over the expression, but leave off any trailing DW_OP_LLVM_fragment. ----
1876 if (Expr) { 0
1877 for (auto Op : Expr->expr_ops()) { 0
1878 switch (Op.getOp()) { 0
1879 default: 0
1880 break; 0
1881 case dwarf::DW_OP_shr: 0
1882 case dwarf::DW_OP_shra: ----
1883 case dwarf::DW_OP_shl: ----
1884 case dwarf::DW_OP_plus: ----
1885 case dwarf::DW_OP_plus_uconst: ----
1886 case dwarf::DW_OP_minus: ----
1887 // We can't safely split arithmetic or shift operations into multiple ----
1888 // fragments because we can't express carry-over between fragments. ----
1889 // ----
1890 // FIXME: We *could* preserve the lowest fragment of a constant offset ----
1891 // operation if the offset fits into SizeInBits. ----
1892 CanSplitValue = false; 0
1893 break; 0
1894 case dwarf::DW_OP_deref: 0
1895 case dwarf::DW_OP_deref_size: ----
1896 case dwarf::DW_OP_deref_type: ----
1897 case dwarf::DW_OP_xderef: ----
1898 case dwarf::DW_OP_xderef_size: ----
1899 case dwarf::DW_OP_xderef_type: ----
1900 // Preceeding arithmetic operations have been applied to compute an ----
1901 // address. It's okay to split the value loaded from that address. ----
1902 CanSplitValue = true; 0
1903 break; 0
1904 case dwarf::DW_OP_stack_value: 0
1905 // Bail if this expression computes a value that cannot be split. ----
1906 if (!CanSplitValue) 0
1907 return std::nullopt; 0
1908 break; 0
1909 case dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_fragment: { 0
1910 // Make the new offset point into the existing fragment. ----
1911 uint64_t FragmentOffsetInBits = Op.getArg(0); 0
1912 uint64_t FragmentSizeInBits = Op.getArg(1); 0
1913 (void)FragmentSizeInBits; ----
1914 assert((OffsetInBits + SizeInBits <= FragmentSizeInBits) && 0
1915 "new fragment outside of original fragment"); ----
1916 OffsetInBits += FragmentOffsetInBits; 0
1917 continue; 0
1918 } 0
1919 } ----
1920 Op.appendToVector(Ops); 0
1921 } ----
1922 } ----
1923 assert((!Expr->isImplicit() || CanSplitValue) && "Expr can't be split"); 0
1924 assert(Expr && "Unknown DIExpression"); 0
1925 Ops.push_back(dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_fragment); 0
1926 Ops.push_back(OffsetInBits); 0
1927 Ops.push_back(SizeInBits); 0
1928 return DIExpression::get(Expr->getContext(), Ops); 0
1929 } 0

1931 std::pair ----
1932 DIExpression::constantFold(const ConstantInt *CI) { 0
1933 // Copy the APInt so we can modify it. ----
1934 APInt NewInt = CI->getValue(); 0
1935 SmallVector Ops; 0
1936 ----
1937 // Fold operators only at the beginning of the expression. ----
1938 bool First = true; 0
1939 bool Changed = false; 0
1940 for (auto Op : expr_ops()) { 0
1941 switch (Op.getOp()) { 0
1942 default: 0
1943 // We fold only the leading part of the expression; if we get to a part ----
1944 // that we're going to copy unchanged, and haven't done any folding, ----
1945 // then the entire expression is unchanged and we can return early. ----
1946 if (!Changed) 0
1947 return {this, CI}; 0
1948 First = false; 0
1949 break; 0
1950 case dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_convert: 0
1951 if (!First) 0
1952 break; 0
1953 Changed = true; 0
1954 if (Op.getArg(1) == dwarf::DW_ATE_signed) 0
1955 NewInt = NewInt.sextOrTrunc(Op.getArg(0)); 0
1956 else { ----
1957 assert(Op.getArg(1) == dwarf::DW_ATE_unsigned && "Unexpected operand"); 0
1958 NewInt = NewInt.zextOrTrunc(Op.getArg(0)); 0
1959 } ----
1960 continue; 0
1961 } ----
1962 Op.appendToVector(Ops); 0
1963 } ----
1964 if (!Changed) 0
1965 return {this, CI}; 0
1966 return {DIExpression::get(getContext(), Ops), 0
1967 ConstantInt::get(getContext(), NewInt)}; 0
1968 } 0

1970 uint64_t DIExpression::getNumLocationOperands() const { 0
1971 uint64_t Result = 0; 0
1972 for (auto ExprOp : expr_ops()) 0

1974 Result = std::max(Result, ExprOp.getArg(0) + 1); 0
1975 assert(hasAllLocationOps(Result) && 0
1976 "Expression is missing one or more location operands."); ----
1977 return Result; 0

1980 std::optional ----
1981 DIExpression::isConstant() const { 0
1982 ----
1983 // Recognize signed and unsigned constants. ----
1984 // An signed constants can be represented as DW_OP_consts C DW_OP_stack_value ----
1985 // (DW_OP_LLVM_fragment of Len). ----
1986 // An unsigned constant can be represented as ----
1987 // DW_OP_constu C DW_OP_stack_value (DW_OP_LLVM_fragment of Len). ----
1988 ----
1989 if ((getNumElements() != 2 && getNumElements() != 3 && 0
1990 getNumElements() != 6) || 0

1992 getElement(0) != dwarf::DW_OP_constu)) 0
1993 return std::nullopt; 0
1994 ----
1995 if (getNumElements() == 2 && getElement(0) == dwarf::DW_OP_consts) 0
1996 return SignedOrUnsignedConstant::SignedConstant; 0
1997 ----
1998 if ((getNumElements() == 3 && getElement(2) != dwarf::DW_OP_stack_value) || 0
1999 (getNumElements() == 6 && (getElement(2) != dwarf::DW_OP_stack_value || 0
2000 getElement(3) != dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_fragment))) 0
2001 return std::nullopt; 0
2002 return getElement(0) == dwarf::DW_OP_constu 0
2003 ? SignedOrUnsignedConstant::UnsignedConstant 0
2004 : SignedOrUnsignedConstant::SignedConstant; 0
2005 } ----
